  "verdict": "CONFIRMATION, NOT CALIBRATION: the independent archeomagnetic predictions correlate with our stack+swing almost as strongly as with the observed record itself, and adding the swing improves every comparison \u2014 the swing is independently CONFIRMED as core-mantle physics. But raw-curve agreement is only ~0.4 and requires a fitted ~300-yr phase lead (a known archeomagnetic systematic), so deriving stack amplitudes/phases from these flows would degrade the eclipse fit. Zero-eclipse-fit via archeomagnetic calibration is not achievable at current field-model quality."
